"```sql\nSELECT \n    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN p.SEX = 'M' AND l.UA <= 8.0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS FLOAT) /\n    NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN p.SEX = 'F' AND l.UA <= 6.5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS male_to_female_ratio\nFROM \n    Patient p\nJOIN \n    Laboratory l ON p.ID = l.ID\nWHERE \n    (p.SEX = 'M' AND l.UA <= 8.0) OR (p.SEX = 'F' AND l.UA <= 6.5);\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the ratio of male to female patients with abnormal uric acid counts by joining the `Patient` and `Laboratory` tables on the `ID` column. It uses conditional aggregation to count the number of male and female patients with abnormal uric acid levels and then divides these counts to get the ratio. The `NULLIF` function is used to prevent division by zero."